COMMENT: An array of ticker symbols under which the security may be traded globally on all exchanges.
An array of PermIDs for the quotes for each exchange where the security is traded. An empty array means that quote information is not available.
The ticker for the primary trading venue of a security. If a security trades on multiple exchanges or has numerous tickers, an attempt is made to select the ticker from the home market.
Broad-based class of the asset, such as 'Ordinary Shares', 'Depositary Receipts', etc.
The exchange name for the primary trading venue of a security.
An array of codes representing the exchanges where the security is traded. An empty array means that exchange information is not available.
The exchange code for the primary trading venue of a security.
Status of the security, i.e. 'Active' or 'Inactive'. An active security is a security that has active quotes and an inactive security has no active quotes. This status changes over time.
